	<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
	<Accordion>
		<AccordionItem title="How long do Widex hearing aids last?">
			<p>
				Most Widex devices last 3–5 years, depending on care, maintenance, and
				daily use. With consistent follow-up appointments, they often last even
				longer.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Do Widex hearing aids help with tinnitus?">
			<p>
				Yes. Many Widex hearing aids include Zen Therapy, a built-in tinnitus
				management program designed to help reduce the perception of ringing or
				buzzing in the ears. Zen Therapy uses soothing background tones and
				customizable soundscapes that can make tinnitus less noticeable,
				especially in quiet environments where it tends to be more bothersome.
			</p>
			<p>
				In addition to sound therapy, Widex hearing aids also amplify
				surrounding environmental sounds, which can help reduce the symptoms of
				tinnitus and make it less prominent throughout the day. The combination
				of amplification and calming sound options allows patients to better
				manage tinnitus while also improving overall hearing clarity and
				comfort.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Can I stream calls and music with Widex?">
			<p>
				Yes. Most Widex devices pair directly with iPhone® and Android™ phones
				for calls, music, and other media. The Widex Moment app also allows
				easy control of settings and programs.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>

